    title: "Exploiting eneio64.sys through physical memory R/W",
    url: "https://xacone.github.io/eneio-driver.html",
    source: "xacone / Yazid",
    category: "Windows Kernel",
    tags: "vulnerable driver byovd physical memory virtual memory hvci eneio64 cve-2020-12446",
    note: "Starts from eneio64.sys exposing physical-memory access and develops the missing machinery needed for useful virtual kernel reads and writes. The walkthrough is a practical reference for locating CR3, translating virtual addresses through page tables, dealing with HVCI and the vulnerable-driver blocklist, and turning a limited driver primitive into an exploitation foundation.",
  },
  {
    title: "Exploiting a vulnerable Lenovo driver (CVE-2025-8061)",
    url: "https://blog.quarkslab.com/exploiting-lenovo-driver-cve-2025-8061.html",
